Indian Utilities Seek 5.8 Million Tons of Coal, India Coal Says

-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 
2011-06-17T04:14:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/indian-utilities-seek-5-8-million-tons-of-coal-india-coal-says.html
Indian power utilities are seeking
to buy as much as 5.8 million metric tons of coal and may award
contracts to a domestic state trading company,  India Coal Market
Watch  said, citing an unidentified official at a trading firm.  Damodar Valley Corp., NTPC-SAIL Power Co. and  Tamil Nadu 
Electricity Board may award contracts this month, the coal
newsletter said, citing the official. Calls to the chairman’s
office at Tamil Nadu, the operations department at Damodar and
NTPC’s switchboard weren’t answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in Singapore at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alexander Kwiatkowski at 
 akwiatkowsk2@bloomberg.net . 